Episodes.Title: ID Parade
Episodes.Plot: UCOS investigate into the death of a policewomen-whose case was closed years ago-following the recovery of the murder weapon from a lake.

Episodes.Title: Painting On Loan
Episodes.Plot:
The discovery of a fake painting in the Queen's art collection sends the UCOS team on a hush-hush mission to uncover the forger. Their investigations swiftly uncover a trail of high class frauds and suspicious deaths, but also lead to suspension for one of the squad.
NOTE: In Scotland This Episode Was Shown On Sunday 11th April Due To LIVE Sportscene Football Being Shown
The UCOS team investigate the murder of a young peace protestor, killed at the outskirts of a nuclear base in 1984, and realise that they may be in danger of exposing a Special Branch cover up.
Episodes.GuestStars: Patrick Baladi, Suzanna Hamilton, Pearce Quigley

Episodes.Title: Good Work Rewarded
Episodes.Plot: The members of a prestigious golf club come under suspicion when the UCOS team investigate a child murder.
Episodes.GuestStars: Isla Blair, Cherie Lunghi, Jamie Glover

Episodes.Title: Home Truths
Episodes.Plot: When a missing person case which Lane originally investigated gets re-activated, he's determined to crack it. But when the team swiftly uncover another two mysterious disappearances, they start to think they've got a serial killer on their hands.
Episodes.GuestStars: Frances Tomelty, Robert Pugh, Philip Martin Brown, Patrick Baladi

Episodes.Title: Talking To The Dead
Episodes.Plot: In an attempt to make contact with his late wife Mary, Jack goes to see a clairvoyant. Instead he meets a girl who died in a shipping container in 1982 and has the case re-opened.
Episodes.GuestStars: Robert Bathurst, Ken Bones, Patrick Baladi

Episodes.Title: Talking to the Dead
Episodes.Plot: Halford visits a clairvoyant in hope of contacting his dead wife but, instead, finds himself communicating with a young girl who disappeared 20 years earlier.
